    {
      "path": "docs/quality/invariants.md",
      "content": "# Architectural Invariants

This document describes the extension contracts and architectural invariants that ensure correctness and extensibility of the workflow engine.

## Registry Contract

The registry contract is implemented by `register_processors` in `src/workflow_engine/runtime/registry.py`. It defines how processors are registered into a runtime dispatcher.

### Invariants
- Only `Processor` instances may be registered.
- Each registered processor must support exactly one distinct channel.
- The default runtime (`build_default_runtime`) registers all channel-specific processors (email, sms, push, webhook) via `register_processors`.

## Processor Inheritance Rules

All processors must inherit from `BaseProcessor`, which enforces the following contract:

### Abstract Requirements
- `supported_channel: str` class attribute must be set to a non-empty string.
- `_deliver(item: WorkItem) -> str` must be implemented for channel-specific side effects.

### Inherited Behavior
- `name` property returns the class name.
- `supports(item)` returns `True` only if `item.channel == supported_channel`.
- `process(item)` delegates to `_deliver` only when supported; otherwise returns a failure `RunResult`.

### Invariants
- No processor may override `supports` or `process` (only `_deliver` is extensible).
- All processors must be subclasses of `BaseProcessor` (verified by `test_default_processors_are_base_processor_subclasses`).
- Each processor must declare a unique `supported_channel` (verified by `test_channels_are_distinct`).

## Repository Contract

The repository contract is defined by `WorkItemRepository` in `src/workflow_engine/contracts/repository.py`.

### Required Methods
- `save(item: WorkItem) -> None`
- `get(identifier: str) -> WorkItem | None`
- `list_by_channel(channel: str) -> list[WorkItem]`
- `list_all() -> list[WorkItem]`

### Invariants
- Implementations must preserve item identity via `identifier`.
- `list_by_channel` must return only items where `item.channel == channel`.
- `save` must not mutate the input item.

## Extension Points

- New processors: subclass `BaseProcessor`, set `supported_channel`, implement `_deliver`.
- New repositories: implement `WorkItemRepository` interface.
- New work item types: subclass `WorkItem` and implement `identifier`, `channel`, `payload`.

All extensions must preserve the invariants above to maintain runtime correctness."
